&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;



&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;RegressionSource&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Regression Source&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The regression appears to have been introduced in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/commit/25c7d0fe6ae20a4c1c42e0cd0b448c08ab03f3fb#diff-722324a11a0e4635a59a9debc962da2c1678d86702a9a106fd0d51188f83853bR317&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;25c7d0fe6ae20a4c1c42e0cd0b448c08ab03f3fb&lt;/a&gt;, which addressed &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-32526&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;SPARK-32526&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;WorkAround&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Work Around&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This regression can be worked around by using &lt;em&gt;Row.isNullAt(int)&lt;/em&gt; and handling the null scenario in user code, prior to calling &lt;em&gt;Row.getSeq(int)&lt;/em&gt; or &lt;em&gt;Row.getList(int)&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
